services.name: Medical Check-up
services.description: Basic medical check-up for health screening and preventive measures.

services.name: Surgery
services.description: A medical procedure in which an incision is made to allow for access to a specific area of the body, typically used to perform a surgical procedure or operation.

services.name: Physiotherapy
services.description: Physical therapy involves a range of exercises, movement and other manual therapies to restore function, prevent contractures, improve flexibility, and enhance the patient's quality of life.

services.name: Vaccination
services.description: Immunization against diseases, such as flu, measles, and tetanus.

services.name: Blood Test
services.description: Examination of a blood sample to check the blood cells and their components.

services.name: ECG (Electrocardiogram)
services.description: Test to record the electrical activity of the heart.

services.name: Dental Check-up
services.description: Examination of the teeth and gums to identify any problems and recommend necessary treatment.
